list.name: Default
list.comment: For some reason, NetworkManager is not getting the facilities ArrayList like it should when called.

task.summary: Finally got Active Inventory to print properly. After some digging, I found out that I was switching the key and value for every Inventory for some reason, which is completely unnecessary. I fixed that and ran the program again, and it worked.

Added Depleted Items and cleaned up code. Depleted Items now print in each Facility Status Output once the amount of the item is at 0. This is not checked, however, until getDepletedItems() is called. Also, changed the return value from ArrayList<String> to HashMap<String, Integer> to work better with getNondepletedItems(). Changed getNondepletedItems() to check for all items that have at least 1 item at the facility. From my testing, it works properly. Without this, getNondepletedItems() was returning a HashMap of all the items of that facility, instead of just the ones that were actually in stock. All outputs were printing twice before, after investigating, it turns out that the issue was each Facility being added twice to the Manager. Removed one of the instances and resolved the issue.
Added 3 more custom orders as per the instructions, and added 3 more facilities as per the second extra credit option
Added and Printed the Order Output without any calculations done on the ordering process.
Moved the middle line down one to make it look better.
Added more 'stuff' to make the output look cleaner and easier to read.
Made Factory methods more like Singletons, Changed FacilityManager and FacilityFactory to NetworkManager and NetworkFactory respectively.
For some reason, NetworkManager is not getting the facilities ArrayList like it should when called.
